oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Capt. Walter Chandler
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This portrait studio image of Walter Chandler shows him in uniform with 30th Div. shoulder patch, captain's bars and Sam Brown belt. Chandler was from Memphis and served as congressman and later mayor. He served in the 114th FA, 30th Div. under Col. Luke Lea of Tennessee, though he was after the war associated with Lea's political rival E. H. "Boss" Crump.
